headlines.description: — Max Strus scored 24 points and made his first six 3-pointers as the Cleveland Cavaliers had their highest-scoring game and most-lopsided victory of the season, routing the Washington Wizards 140-101 on Wednesday night to open a two-game set.
headlines.shortLinkText: Max Strus scores 24 points, Cavaliers rout Wizards 140-101

headlines.description: — All-Star guard Tyrese Haliburton wanted to reinforce that Indiana's success against Milwaukee wasn't a fluke.
headlines.shortLinkText: Pacers pull away with 47-point 3rd quarter, beat Bucks 142-130 for 5th straight win

events.name: Oklahoma City Thunder at Atlanta Hawks

headlines.description: — Jalen Johnson scored a career-high 28 points and the Atlanta Hawks held off Oklahoma City 141-138 on Wednesday night, ending the Thunder’s five-game winning streak.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jalen Johnson has career-high 28 points as Hawks hold on late, snap Thunder's 5-game winning streak

headlines.description: — Alperen Sengun scored 30 points and Fred VanVleet added 21 points and 10 assists as the Houston Rockets beat the Brooklyn Nets 112-101 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Alperen Sengun scores 30 points as Rockets hand Nets fifth straight loss, 112-101

headlines.description: — Immanuel Quickley scored 26 points, Pascal Siakam added 24 and the Toronto Raptors weathered a late Memphis rally to defeat the Grizzlies 116-111 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Immanuel Quickley scores 26, Pascal Siakam adds 24 as Raptors hold on to defeat Grizzlies 116-111

events.name: New Orleans Pelicans at Minnesota Timberwolves

headlines.description: — Zion Williamson scored 27 points and the New Orleans Pelicans kept rolling with a 117-106 victory over the West-leading Minnesota Timberwolves on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Zion Williamson scores 27 points, Pelicans beat West-leading Timberwolves 117-106

events.name: Chicago Bulls at New York Knicks

headlines.description: — Julius Randle scored 35 points, Jalen Brunson had 31 points and 13 assists and the New York Knicks beat the Chicago Bulls 116-100 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Julius Randle, Jalen Brunson help Knicks beat Bulls, 116-100

events.name: Portland Trail Blazers at Dallas Mavericks

headlines.description: — Luka Doncic scored 30 of his 41 points in the first half, Kyrie Irving added 29 in his second game back from a heel injury and the Dallas Mavericks routed the Portland Trail Blazers 126-97 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Doncic scores 41 and Irving adds 29 as Mavs blow out Trail Blazers 126-97

headlines.description: — Los Angeles coach Tyronn Lue was still stewing a little in the postgame press conference, replaying in his head how the Clippers' offense got a little stagnant during the final eight minutes against Phoenix on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: George scores 33 points, Leonard adds 30 to help surging Clippers beat Suns 131-122

headlines.description: — Jordan Clarkson scored 29 of his 36 points after halftime and Lauri Markkanen added 31 as the Utah Jazz outlasted the tough-luck Detroit Pistons 154-148 in overtime on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Clarkson scores 36, Jazz outlast hard-luck Pistons in OT, 154-148

events.name: Miami Heat at Los Angeles Lakers

headlines.description: — Tyler Herro scored 21 points, Duncan Robinson had 11 of his 13 points in the fourth quarter and the Miami Heat beat the Los Angeles Lakers 110-96 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Tyler Herro scores 21 points, Heat pull away in 4th quarter to beat Lakers 110-96

headlines.description: — Domantas Sabonis had 22 points, 23 rebounds and 12 assists, Malik Monk scored 37 off the bench and the Sacramento Kings outlasted the Orlando Magic 138-135 in double overtime Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Kings outlast short-handed Magic in double overtime behind triple-double from Domantas Sabonis
